attributeDefinition.name: userName
attributeDefinition.description: Unique identifier for the User, typically used by the user to directly authenticate to the service provider. Each User MUST include a non-empty userName value. This identifier MUST be unique across the service provider's entire set of Users.

attributeDefinition.name: name
attributeDefinition.description: The components of the user's real name. Providers MAY return just the full name as a single string in the formatted sub-attribute, or they MAY return just the individual component attributes using the other sub-attributes, or they MAY return both.  If both variants are returned, they SHOULD be describing the same name, with the formatted name indicating how the component attributes should be combined.

attributeDefinition.name: formatted
attributeDefinition.description: The full name, including all middle names, titles, and suffixes as appropriate, formatted for display (e.g., 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributeDefinition.name: familyName
attributeDefinition.description: The family name of the User, or last name in most Western languages (e.g., 'Jensen' given the full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributeDefinition.name: givenName
attributeDefinition.description: The given name of the User, or first name in most Western languages (e.g., 'Barbara' given the full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributeDefinition.name: middleName
attributeDefinition.description: The middle name(s) of the User (e.g., 'Jane' given the full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributeDefinition.name: honorificPrefix
attributeDefinition.description: The honorific prefix(es) of the User, or title in most Western languages (e.g., 'Ms.' given the full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributeDefinition.name: honorificSuffix
attributeDefinition.description: The honorific suffix(es) of the User, or suffix in most Western languages (e.g., 'III' given the full name 'Ms. Barbara J Jensen, III').

attributeDefinition.name: displayName
attributeDefinition.description: The name of the User, suitable for display to end-users.  The name SHOULD be the full name of the User being described, if known.

attributeDefinition.name: nickName
attributeDefinition.description: The casual way to address the user in real life, e.g., 'Bob' or 'Bobby' instead of 'Robert'.  This attribute SHOULD NOT be used to represent a User's username (e.g., 'bjensen' or 'mpepperidge'

attributeDefinition.name: profileUrl
attributeDefinition.description: A fully qualified URL pointing to a page representing the User's online profile.

attributeDefinition.name: title
attributeDefinition.description: The user's title, such as 'Vice President.'

attributeDefinition.name: userType
attributeDefinition.description: Used to identify the relationship between the organization and the user. Typical values used might be 'Contractor', 'Employee', 'Intern', 'Temp', 'External', and 'Unknown', but any value may be used.

attributeDefinition.name: preferredLanguage
attributeDefinition.description: Indicates the User's preferred written or spoken language.  Generally used for selecting a localized user interface; e.g., 'en_US' specifies the language English and country US.

attributeDefinition.name: locale
attributeDefinition.description: Used to indicate the User's default location for purposes of localizing items such as currency, date time format, or numerical representations.

attributeDefinition.name: timezone
attributeDefinition.description: The User's time zone in the 'Olson' time zone database format, e.g., 'America/Los_Angeles'.

attributeDefinition.name: active
attributeDefinition.description: A Boolean value indicating the User's administrative status.

attributeDefinition.name: password
attributeDefinition.description: The User's cleartext password. This attribute is intended to be used as a means to specify an initial password when creating a new User or to reset an existing User's password.

attributeDefinition.name: emails
attributeDefinition.description: Email addresses for the user. The value SHOULD be canonicalized by the service provider, e.g., 'bjensen@example.com' instead of 'bjensen@EXAMPLE.COM'.

attributeDefinition.name: value
attributeDefinition.description: Email addresses for the user. The value SHOULD be canonicalized by the service provider, e.g., 'bjensen@example.com' instead of 'bjensen@EXAMPLE.COM'.

attributeDefinition.name: display
attributeDefinition.description: A human-readable name, primarily used for display purposes.

attributeDefinition.name: type
attributeDefinition.description: A label indicating the attribute's function, e.g., 'work' or 'home'.

attributeDefinition.name: primary
attributeDefinition.description: A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred mailing address or primary email address. The primary attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributeDefinition.name: phoneNumbers
attributeDefinition.description: Phone numbers for the User. The value SHOULD be canonicalized by the service provider according to the format specified in RFC 3966, e.g., 'tel:+1-201-555-0123'.

attributeDefinition.name: value
attributeDefinition.description: Phone number of the User.

attributeDefinition.name: display
attributeDefinition.description: A human-readable name, primarily used for display purposes.

attributeDefinition.name: type
attributeDefinition.description: A label indicating the attribute's function, e.g., 'work', 'home', 'mobile'.

attributeDefinition.name: primary
attributeDefinition.description: A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred mailing address or primary email address. The primary attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributeDefinition.name: ims
attributeDefinition.description: Instant messaging addresses for the User.

attributeDefinition.name: value
attributeDefinition.description: Instant messaging address for the User.

attributeDefinition.description: A human-readable name, primarily used for display purposes.

attributeDefinition.name: type
attributeDefinition.description: A label indicating the attribute's function, e.g., 'aim', 'gtalk', 'xmpp'.

attributeDefinition.name: primary
attributeDefinition.description: A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred mailing address or primary email address. The primary attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributeDefinition.name: photos
attributeDefinition.description: URLs of photos of the User.

attributeDefinition.name: value
attributeDefinition.description: URLs of a photo of the User.

attributeDefinition.name: type
attributeDefinition.description: A label indicating the attribute's function, i.e., 'photo' or 'thumbnail'.

attributeDefinition.name: primary
attributeDefinition.description: A Boolean value indicating the 'primary' or preferred attribute value for this attribute, e.g., the preferred mailing address or primary email address. The primary attribute value 'true' MUST appear no more than once.

attributeDefinition.name: addresses
attributeDefinition.description: A physical mailing address for this User.

attributeDefinition.name: formatted
attributeDefinition.description: The full mailing address, formatted for display or use with a mailing label. This attribute MAY contain newlines.

attributeDefinition.name: streetAddress
attributeDefinition.description: The full street address component, which may include house number, street name, P.O. box, and multi-line extended street address information. This attribute MAY contain newlines.

attributeDefinition.name: locality
attributeDefinition.description: The city or locality component.

attributeDefinition.name: region
attributeDefinition.description: The state or region component.

attributeDefinition.name: postalCode
attributeDefinition.description: The zip code or postal code component.

attributeDefinition.name: country
attributeDefinition.description: The country name component.

attributeDefinition.name: type
attributeDefinition.description: A label indicating the attribute's function, e.g., 'work' or 'home'.

attributeDefinition.name: groups
attributeDefinition.description: A list of groups to which the user belongs, either through direct membership, through nested groups, or dynamically calculated.

attributeDefinition.name: value
attributeDefinition.description: The identifier of the User's group.

attributeDefinition.name: $ref
attributeDefinition.description: The URI of the corresponding 'Group' resource to which the user belongs.

attributeDefinition.name: display

attributeDefinition.name: type
attributeDefinition.description: A label indicating the attribute's function, e.g., 'direct' or 'indirect'.

attributeDefinition.name: entitlements
attributeDefinition.description: A list of entitlements for the User that represent a thing the User has.

attributeDefinition.name: value
attributeDefinition.description: The value of an entitlement.

attributeDefinition.name: roles
attributeDefinition.description: A list of roles for the User that collectively represent who the User is, e.g., 'Student', 'Faculty'.
